The paper deals with abnormal event detection in videos using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and learning generic knowledge about visual concepts. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques for anomaly detection, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of CNNs for learning visual concepts and anomaly detection also suggests that the paper could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper involves analyzing videos, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves recounting abnormal events, which could involve natural language processing techniques and thus could belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
